conditions below.

1. Attribution
Any use or implementation of the IDDAS Protocol must clearly attribute
the protocol to its original author and source repository.

2. No Silent Modification
The protocol text, rules, or specifications may not be modified and
redistributed under the name “IDDAS” or “IDDAS Protocol” without
explicit written permission from the author.

3. Version Integrity
If modifications or extensions are made for internal or experimental
use, they must be clearly marked as non-canonical and must not be
presented as an official version of the IDDAS Protocol.

4. Forward-Only Changes
No modification may be represented as retroactively altering the
meaning, outcomes, or rules of prior versions of the protocol.

5. No Warranty
The protocol is provided “as is”, without warranty of any kind, express
or implied.

This license governs the protocol specification only. Implementations,
applications, and services referencing the protocol are not covered by
this license unless explicitly stated.
